title: U.S. wind power generation 2000 to 2018
yAxis: Net generation in billion kilowatt hours
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Net generation in billion kilowatt hours. In total the number of data points it has is 19.
In general Net generation in billion kilowatt hours has rose over the Year.

Net generation in billion kilowatt hours is roughly increasing from 2000 to 2002, roughly constant from 2002 to 2003, rapidly increasing from 2003 to 2012, and lastly roughly constant from 2012 to 2018.
The highest Net generation in billion kilowatt hours, of value 274.95 was reached at Year 2018
The lowest Net generation in billion kilowatt hours, of value 5.59 was reported at Year 2000
